<p>I'm developing an hybrid application (platforms: browser, android, IOS) using cordova. Now if a user try to access my app with any browser from their android mobile then i want to check whether they have installed my app already if installed i want to open the installed app.</p>  <p>Otherwise i want to show a text on top of my app that an app is available please download from market. If they clicked then it should open playstore app and one particular page to download. </p>  <p>like this i want to show in browser</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/oMwqw.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/oMwqw.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Im using cordova. I tried using following plugins but it works only from an android app. like from one app i can check another app is installed or not but not from a browser.</p>  <p><a href="https://github.com/lampaa/com.lampa.startapp" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/lampaa/com.lampa.startapp</a></p>  <p><a href="https://github.com/apache/cordova-plugin-inappbrowser" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/apache/cordova-plugin-inappbrowser</a>  <code>//to open the app</code></p>  <p><a href="https://github.com/ohh2ahh/AppAvailability" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/ohh2ahh/AppAvailability</a></p>  <p>For example i tried with twitter app. </p>  <p>I tried two solutions</p>  <p>CODE 1:</p>  <pre><code>                // to check app is installed or not                 navigator.startApp.check("com.twitter.android",  // URI Scheme                 function(message) {  // Success callback                     navigator.startApp.start("com.twitter.android", function(message) {                      console.log(message);                      },                      function(error) {                        console.log(error);                      }); */                 },                 function(error) {  // Error callback                     cordova.InAppBrowser.open('market://details?id=com.twitter.android', '_system', 'location=no');                 }); </code></pre>  <p>CODE 2:</p>  <pre><code>                  // to check app is installed or not                   appAvailability.check("com.twitter.android", // URI Scheme                        function() {  // Success callback                         navigator.startApp.start("com.twitter.android", function(message) {                               console.log(message); // =&gt; OK                           },                           function(error) {                               console.log(error);                           });                        },                       function() {  // Error callback                          cordova.InAppBrowser.open('https://twitter.com', '_system', 'location=no');                          console.log('Twitter is not available');                       }                     ); </code></pre>  <p>No error in code, i can build correctly and i can debug and check in desktop chrome browser the only thing is it is not working.</p>  <p>Please help me..</p>